(90, 1, '2016-10-26 18:47:53', '2016-10-26 18:47:53', 'As you may or may not know is that I have been on assignment in Stockholm, Sweden this year.  Being here I had the opportunity to experiment and try new things.  In this post I bring my point of view on 2 new services that have been recently stated in Stockholm.  One is from the USA and another is from Germany.\r\n\r\n<img class=" wp-image-80" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/uberEatsIcon.png" alt="Uber Eats Icon" width="60" height="55" />I''ll start by Uber Eats:\r\n\r\nI am a long time user of Uber ride sharing services.  I have used the service in many cities throughout the world whilst traveling for work.  Overall I''m quite satisfied with the service. I wasn''t acquainted the the Uber Eats service until I got an email - in swedish - from Uber saying that because I have used the service for a long time that they were giving out this cupom code that I could use to order food and try out the service.\r\n\r\nUber is starting in Stockholm.  They are giving out a cupom code that you can use up to 3 times and it gives 50 SEK (~US$5.50) discount.  The delivery is free for now.  Most likely it will change once they get established in this market.\r\n\r\nI decided to give the service a try.  I downloaded the app, it recognized me as a customer. I never logged on to the Uber Eats app.  All my profiles (business and personal) were automatically loaded which was really nice.  First thing I did was to register the cupom.  From there I browsed the menu available.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-84" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5874.png" alt="Menu " width="250" height="428" />\r\n\r\nThe menu was somewhat limited and showed a lot of options that were grayed out with the description "currently not available".  I decided to go with the "Libanon Gruill &amp; Meza".  One thing that was a bit strange is that I had never heard about the restaurant and I couldn''t find anywhere in the app the address of the restaurants shown.  I was basing by filter on the time window it shows on the lower right hand corner of each picture.\r\n\r\nSure enough, I selected the "Mixed Platter 3" option.  It was nice that I could put a note to the restaurant to avoid the garlic cream (usually they are very strong and I keep reminding of it the whole day).  Total of the order was 120 SEK.  0 SEK delivery and -50 SEK because of that cupom that I registered as soon as I downloaded the app.  Total to pay: 70 SEK (Way cheaper than what I usually spend for lunch time)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-85" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5875.png" alt="img_5875" width="250" height="428" /><img class="wp-image-87" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5877.png" alt="img_5877" width="250" height="428" /></center>&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFrom this point onward it was a mix like ordering food from any other food delivery app and waiting for an Uber ride.  The first follow-up notifications you get are more food related.  It first says that the order is being confirmed by the restaurant.  During this time you can still cancel the order.  From there on, you are already charged for the food. Once the order is accepted by the restaurant you move to the status "Food is being prepared".\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-83" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5873.png" alt="Uber Eats" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-86" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5876.png" alt="Uber Eats" width="250" height="428" /></center>\r\nThe next step is when a driver gets assigned to your order. As soon as a driver is assigned the feeling is more like waiting for a normal Uber ride. The funny thing is that instead of seeing the icon of a car, you see a knife and fork icon.  I thought that was where the restaurant was located. But as soon as it started moving I realized it was the car. :)\r\n\r\nUber Eats stops in front of the address that you provide.  They don''t go to your door step.  At least that''s the general rule.  I believe that in more suburban areas they can do it differently, but since I''m in downtown Stockholm there''s no way for them to park anywhere.\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-78" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5879.png" alt="Uber Eats - driver assigned" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-79" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5880.png" alt="Uber Eats - driver assigned" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-77" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5878.png" alt="Uber Eats - driver assigned" width="250" height="428" /></center>&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe presentation of the food in nothing pleasing to eye.  It comes in a brown paper bag.  Inside is the Styrofoam container and the food all together in there. Nothing similar to the picture I clicked in the beginning.  But hey, what you want is to eat, right?\r\n\r\n<img class=" wp-image-81" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/uberEatsPresentation.jpg" alt="Uber Eats Presentation" width="534" height="300" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBy the way, if you''d like to try Uber Eats in your area you may use the cupom code <strong>Valkommen150</strong> to get the 150 SEK discount (50 SEK for your first 3 orders). This cupom is valid only in Sweden and until November 2nd, 2016.  If you are from anywhere in the world or if you ready this after November 2nd, you may use cupom <strong>eats-ivand850ue</strong> to get a good discount on your first order with Uber Eats.  The value depends on where you are.  In Sweden it gives 100 SEK discount and in Canada it''s $10.00 off.\r\n\r\n<img class=" wp-image-82" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/foodoraIcon.png" alt="Foodora Icon" width="60" height="60" /> Foodora:', 'Uber Eats vs. Foodora', ' In this post I bring my point of view on 2 new services that have been recently started in Stockholm.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '71-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-26 18:47:53', '2016-10-26 18:47:53', '', 71, 'https://ivanjr.website/71-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
