 couldn''t find anywhere in the app the address of the restaurants shown.  I was basing my filter on the time window it showed on the lower right hand corner of each picture.\r\n\r\nSure enough, I selected the "Mixed Platter 3" option.  It was nice that I could put a note to the restaurant to avoid the garlic cream (usually they are very strong and I keep reminding of it the whole day).  Total of the order was 120 SEK.  0 SEK delivery and -50 SEK because of that cupom that I registered as soon as I downloaded the app.  Total to pay: 70 SEK (way cheaper than what I usually spend for lunch time)\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-85" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5875.png" alt="img_5875" width="250" height="428" /><img class="wp-image-87" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5877.png" alt="img_5877" width="250" height="428" /></center>&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFrom this point onward it was a mix like ordering food from any other food delivery app and waiting for an Uber ride.  The first follow-up notifications you get are more food related.  It first says that the order is being confirmed by the restaurant.  During this time you can still cancel the order.  From there on, you are already charged for the food. Once the order is accepted by the restaurant you move to the status "Food is being prepared".\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-83" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5873.png" alt="Uber Eats" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-86" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5876.png" alt="Uber Eats" width="250" height="428" /></center>\r\nThe next step is when a driver gets assigned to your order. As soon as a driver is assigned the feeling is more like waiting for a normal Uber ride. The funny thing is that instead of seeing the icon of a car, you see a knife and fork icon.  I thought that was where the restaurant was located. But as soon as it started moving I realized it was the car. :)\r\n\r\nUber Eats stops in front of the address that you provide.  They don''t go to your door step.  At least that''s the general rule.  I believe that in more suburban areas they can do it differently, but since I''m in downtown Stockholm there''s no way for them to park anywhere.\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-78" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5879.png" alt="Uber Eats - driver assigned" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-79" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5880.png" alt="Uber Eats - driver assigned" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-77" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5878.png" alt="Uber Eats - driver assigned" width="250" height="428" /></center>&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe presentation of the food in nothing pleasing to eye.  It comes in a brown paper bag.  Inside is the Styrofoam container and the food all together in there. Nothing similar to the picture I clicked in the beginning.  But hey, what you want is to eat, right?\r\n\r\n<img class=" wp-image-81" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/uberEatsPresentation.jpg" alt="Uber Eats Presentation" width="534" height="300" />\r\n\r\nI was expecting the star-rating system as we have in the ride sharing app, but here the evaluation was just thumbs-up or thumbs-down to both the driver and the restaurant.\r\n\r\nBy the way, if you''d like to try Uber Eats in your area you may use the cupom code <strong>Valkommen150</strong> to get the 150 SEK discount (50 SEK for your first 3 orders). This cupom is valid only in Sweden and until November 2nd, 2016.  If you are from anywhere else in the world or if you read this post after November 2nd, you may use cupom <strong>eats-ivand850ue</strong> to get a good discount on your first order with Uber Eats.  The value depends on where you are.  In Sweden it gives 100 SEK discount and in Canada it''s $10.00 off.  If you use this second code I get something also.  I think it''s the same discount as you get, but I just don''t know yet for real because no one has used my code by the time of this post''s writing.\r\n\r\n<img class=" wp-image-82" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/foodoraIcon.png" alt="Foodora Icon" width="60" height="60" /> Foodora:\r\n\r\nWith Foodora I must say the experience is a bit more pleasing.  The look-and-feel of the app is really nice.  Different from Uber Eats that rely on cars, Foodora comes by bike.  Yes, by bycicle!  It''s currently 3°C outside and these guys are out there biking the city doing deliveries.  It''s nice to know that by ordering with them you''re contributing less to the increase of our carbon footprint.  Here there is a fixed delivery fee of 49 SEK (~US$5).  No way out of this one.  Even if you have a promo code or cupom code it''s on top of the total value food + delivery.\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-94" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5897.png" alt="foodora initial screen" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-95" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5898.png" alt="foodora menu" width="250" height="428" />\r\n</center>Foodora has been here in Stockholm for much longer period than Uber Eats.  Their options of restaurants is much wider and I must confess that all look much nicer than what was available in Uber Eats.  This time I had no promo code so I''m paying the full price.   One thing that is nice is that you have the option to either use the app of the website.  This is good so it''s more versatile rather than just relying on the phone.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-105" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Capture.png" alt="foodora web" width="961" height="389" />\r\n\r\nThe process after you order is similar to any food delivery system.  The steps here are 1) Your order has been received, 2) The restaurant is preparing your food, 3) Your order has been picked up for delivery and 4) Order is arriving soon! I found that the countdown timer here is less reliable.  It keeps changing.\r\n<img class="wp-image-106 alignnone" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5899.png" alt="foodora app" width="250" height="428" /><img class="wp-image-107 alignnone" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5900.png" alt="foodora app" width="250" height="428" />\r\n\r\nAnother difference from Uber Eats is that Foodora does arrive at your door step. Even here in downtown Stockholm they can come in (if you open the door''s building or put in the order the note to the biker of the code to open the door - not advisable).  Although if you down and pick up the order they really appreciate it.\r\n\r\nWith foodora you can see where the biker that is going to pick up your order is.  In Uber Eats you know who the person is, you see even his/her photo.  In foodora you only know the name of the biker if you check on the web version.  I couldn''t find it in the app version.  Another information that I could only find in the web version is the order number.  This is important in case something goes wrong with your order and you need to contact support.  Once I ordered the drink also and it didn''t come.  Via the "contact support" everything was solve quickly via chat.  I was refunded the value of the drink directly on my credit card.\r\n\r\nNow the presentation.  Again here nothing spetacular.  The same brown bag, but now with', 'Uber Eats vs. Foodora', ' In this post I bring my point of view on 2 new services that have been recently started in Stockholm.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '71-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-26 20:28:40', '2016-10-26 20:28:40', '', 71, 'https://ivanjr.website/71-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
