ring your food, 3) Your order has been picked up for delivery and 4) Order is arriving soon! I found that the countdown timer here is less reliable.  It keeps changing.\r\n<img class="wp-image-106 alignnone" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5899.png" alt="foodora app" width="250" height="428" /><img class="wp-image-107 alignnone" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5900.png" alt="foodora app" width="250" height="428" />\r\n\r\nAnother difference from Uber Eats is that Foodora does arrive at your door step. Even here in downtown Stockholm they can come in (if you open the door''s building or put in the order the note to the biker of the code to open the door - not advisable).  Although if you down and pick up the order they really appreciate it.\r\n\r\n<img class="wp-image-99 alignnone" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5903.png" alt="foodora app" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-100 alignnone" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5904.png" alt="foodora app" width="250" height="428" /><img class="wp-image-101 alignnone" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5905.png" alt="foodora app" width="250" height="428" />\r\n\r\nWith foodora you can see where the biker that is going to pick up your order is.  In Uber Eats you know who the person is, you see even his/her photo.  In foodora you only know the name of the biker if you check on the web version.  I couldn''t find it in the app version.  Another information that I could only find in the web version is the order number.  This is important in case something goes wrong with your order and you need to contact support.  Once I ordered the drink also and it didn''t come.  Via the "contact support" everything was solve quickly via chat.  I was refunded the value of the drink directly on my credit card.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_109" align="aligncenter" width="607"]<img class="size-full wp