(119, 1, '2016-10-31 02:47:23', '2016-10-31 02:47:23', 'What you may or may not know is that I have been on assignment in Stockholm, Sweden this year.  Being here I had the opportunity to experiment and try new things.  In this post I bring my point of view on 2 new services that have been recently launched in Stockholm.  One is from the USA and another is from Germany.\r\n\r\n<img class=" wp-image-80" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/uberEatsIcon.png" alt="Uber Eats Icon" width="60" height="55" />I''ll start by Uber Eats:\r\n\r\nI am a long time user of Uber ride sharing services.  I have used the service in many cities throughout the world whilst traveling for work.  Overall I''m quite satisfied with the service. I wasn''t acquainted with the Uber Eats service until I got an email - in Swedish - from Uber saying that because I have used the service for a long time that they were giving out this coupon code that I could use to order food and try out the service.\r\n\r\nUber Eats is starting in Stockholm.  They are giving out a coupon code that you can use up to 3 times and it gives 50 SEK (~US$5.50) discount.  The delivery is free for now.  Most likely it will change once they get established in this market.\r\n\r\nI decided to give the service a try.  I downloaded the app, it recognized me as a customer. I never logged on to the Uber Eats app.  All my profiles (business and personal) were automatically loaded which was really nice.  First thing I did was to register the coupon.  From there I browsed the menu available.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-84" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5874.png" alt="Menu " width="250" height="428" />\r\n\r\nThe menu was somewhat limited and showed a lot of options that were grayed out with the description "currently not available".  I decided to go with the "Libanon Grill &amp; Meza".  One thing that was a bit strange is that I had never heard about the restaurant before and I couldn''t find anywhere in the app the address of the restaurants shown.  I was basing my filter on the time window it showed on the lower right hand corner of each picture.\r\n\r\nSure enough, I selected the "Mixed Platter 3" option.  It was nice that I could put a note to the restaurant to avoid the garlic cream (usually they are very strong and I keep reminding of it the whole day).  Total of the order was 120 SEK.  0 SEK delivery and -50 SEK because of that coupon that I registered as soon as I downloaded the app.  Total to pay: 70 SEK (way cheaper than what I usually spend for lunch time)\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-85" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5875.png" alt="img_5875" width="250" height="428" /><img class="wp-image-87" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5877.png" alt="img_5877" width="250" height="428" /></center>&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFrom this point onward it was a mix like ordering food from any other food delivery app and waiting for an Uber ride.  The first follow-up notifications you get are more food related.  It first says that the order is being confirmed by the restaurant.  During this time you can still cancel the order.  From there on, you are already charged for the food. Once the order is accepted by the restaurant you move to the status "Food is being prepared".\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-83" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5873.png" alt="Uber Eats" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-86" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5876.png" alt="Uber Eats" width="250" height="428" /></center>\r\nThe next step is when a driver gets assigned to your order. As soon as a driver is assigned the feeling is more like waiting for a normal Uber ride. The funny thing is that instead of seeing the icon of a car, you see a knife and fork icon.  I thought that was where the restaurant was located. But as soon as it started moving I realized it was the car. :)\r\n\r\nUber Eats stops in front of the address that you provide.  They don''t go to your door step.  At least that''s the general rule.  I believe that in more suburban areas they can do it differently, but since I''m in downtown Stockholm there''s no way for them to park anywhere.\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-78" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5879.png" alt="Uber Eats - driver assigned" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-79" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5880.png" alt="Uber Eats - driver assigned" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-77" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5878.png" alt="Uber Eats - driver assigned" width="250" height="428" /></center>&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe presentation of the food is nothing pleasing to eye.  It comes in a brown paper bag.  Inside is the Styrofoam container and the food all together in there. Nothing similar to the picture I clicked in the beginning.  But hey, what you want is to eat, right?\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class=" wp-image-81" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/uberEatsPresentation.jpg" alt="Uber Eats Presentation" width="534" height="300" /></center><center></center>I was expecting the star-rating system as we have in the ride sharing app, but here the evaluation was just thumbs-up or thumbs-down to both the driver and the restaurant.\r\n\r\nBy the way, if you''d like to try Uber Eats in your area you may use the coupon code <strong>Valkommen150</strong> to get the 150 SEK discount (50 SEK for your first 3 orders). This coupon is valid only in Sweden and until November 2nd, 2016.  If you are from anywhere else in the world or if you read this post after November 2nd, you may use coupon <strong>eats-ivand850ue</strong> to get a good discount on your first order with Uber Eats.  The value depends on where you are.  In Sweden it gives 100 SEK discount and in Canada it''s $10.00 off.  If you use this second code I get something also.  I think it''s the same discount as you get, but I just don''t know yet for real because no one has used my code by the time of this post''s writing.\r\n\r\n<img class=" wp-image-82" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/foodoraIcon.png" alt="Foodora Icon" width="60" height="60" /> Foodora:\r\n\r\nWith Foodora I must say the experience is a bit more pleasing.  The look-and-feel of the app is really nice.  Different from Uber Eats that rely on cars, Foodora comes by bike.  Yes, by bicycle!  It''s currently 3°C outside and these guys are out there biking the city doing deliveries.  It''s nice to know that by ordering with them you''re contributing less to the increase of our carbon footprint.  Here there is a fixed delivery fee of 49 SEK (~US$5).  No way out of this one.  Even if you have a promo code or coupon code it''s on top of the total value food + delivery.\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-94" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5897.png" alt="foodora initial screen" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-95" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5898.png" alt="foodora menu" width="250" height="428" /></center>Foodora has been here in Stockholm for much longer period than Uber Eats.  Their options of restaurants is much wider and I must confess that all look much nicer than what was available in Uber Eats.  This time I had no promo code so I''m paying the full price.   One thing that is nice is that you have the option to either use the app of the website.  This is good so it''s more versatile rather than just relying on the phone.\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-105" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Capture.png" alt="foodora web" width="961" height="389" /></center>The process after you order is similar to any food delivery system.  The steps here are 1) Your order has been received, 2) The restaurant is preparing your food, 3) Your order has been picked up for delivery and 4) Order is arriving soon! I found that the countdown timer here is less reliable.  It keeps changing.\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-106" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5899.png" alt="foodora app" width="250" height="428" /><img class="wp-image-107" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5900.png" alt="foodora app" width="250" height="428" /></center>Another difference from Uber Eats is that Foodora does arrive at your door step. Even here in downtown Stockholm they can come in (if you open the door''s building or put in the order the note to the biker of the code to open the door - not advisable).  Although if you go down and pick up the order they really appreciate it.\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="wp-image-99" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5903.png" alt="foodora app" width="250" height="428" /> <img class="wp-image-100" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5904.png" alt="foodora app" width="250" height="428" /><img class="wp-image-101" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_5905.png" alt="foodora app" width="250" height="428" /></center>With foodora you can see where the biker that is going to pick up your order is.  In Uber Eats you know who the person is, you see even his/her photo.  In foodora you only know the name of the biker if you check on the web version.  I couldn''t find it in the app version.  Another information that I could only find in the web version is the order number.  This is important in case something goes wrong with your order and you need to contact support.  Once I ordered the drink also and it didn''t come.  Via the "contact support" everything was solve quickly via chat.  I was refunded the value of the drink directly on my credit card.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_109" align="aligncenter" width="607"]<img class="size-full wp-image-109" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Capture-1.png" alt="foodora reimbursement" width="607" height="292" /> foodora reimbursement: (25 SEK ~ CAD$3.72)[/caption]\r\n\r\nNow the presentation.  Again here nothing spectacular.  The same brown bag, but with reddish purple color print usually comes, but this time it was a white bag from the restaurant only.  I ordered a burger, so nothing on container here.  This time I had ordered soft drink also.\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-93" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/foodoraPresentation.jpg" alt="foodora presentation" width="1280" height="720" /></center>The cherry on the cake is the wet towel to clean the hands that comes.  I didn''t use it because I ordered at home and I used my own napkins and washed properly the hands after eating so I could finish this post. ;) At least it''s saved for a later time when I need it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Promo Code time</strong>: if you want to try out foodora and get 100 SEK for your first order you can use the promo code by clicking on this link: <strong><a href="https://bnc.lt/YR5e/LmdlpNa3cx">https://bnc.lt/YR5e/LmdlpNa3cx</a> </strong>\r\nIt will also work if you are from else in the world, the value will be the 100 SEK in your local currency.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCONCLUSION:\r\n\r\nI have ordered two different types of dishes to compare on the presentation piece.  But as a service for you I guess it really matters to what restaurants they have done agreements with.  The delivery type and even delivery time was about the same for both (~35min).  It''s good foodora with the lower carbon footprint, but in really cold weather or even rainy weather I''d feel sorry for the biker.  From a consumer perspective go and use the one that provides you the best relation price X quality of food.  I''ve shared coupons for both for you to try if you haven''t already.\r\n\r\nI''ve heard that from the deliver''s point of view they are really different services and in theory on the long run foodora is better than Uber even if they need support from the company.  I cannot say anything on this since I have never done a gig with any of them.', 'Uber Eats vs. Foodora', ' In this post I bring my point of view on 2 new services that have been recently started in Stockholm.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '71-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-31 02:47:23', '2016-10-31 02:47:23', '', 71, 'https://ivanjr.website/71-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(121, 1, '2016-11-08 14:45:29', '2016-11-08 14:45:29', 'Okay, Many of you have seen the <strong>#FF</strong> on the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twitter">bird''s social network</a>, but you never quite understand what it is and how it''s used for.  I''ll try to describe to you what it should be and also what it is.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignright" src="http://www.salvadorpuig.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Follow-Friday.jpg" />#FF is short for #FollowFriday. It’s a Twitter trend created back in 2009 by Twitter users that has since become a customary Friday activity.\r\n\r\nAn #FF is a shout out, a show of appreciation, a nice thing to do.\r\n\r\nThe idea is that each Friday, you recommend Twitter profiles that you appreciate or think it''s useful to all of your followers. Your #FF recommendation will encourage others to check out that profile, generating more followers for them. That''s why it''s considered to be a nice thing to do.\r\n\r\nThe # (hashtag) is added to create a clickable link and group all the #FF (or #FollowFriday) messages on Twitter together making them easily searchable. If you want to send an #FF, simply add #FF (or #FollowFriday) to your message, the @name of the person you are recommending along with a description as to why you are recommending\r\n\r\nOne good #FF example:\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-127" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ff_good_1.jpg" alt="ff_good_1" width="589" height="152" />\r\n\r\nOr even a more political one is also good:\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-126" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ff_good.jpg" alt="#FF" width="584" height="102" />\r\n<blockquote><em><strong>Tip:</strong> Try to include just one recommendation per message, rather than a message full of @names which is often counter productive, like this one:</em></blockquote>\r\nNow let''s see a bad #FF example:\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-128" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ff_bad.jpg" alt="#FF bad one" width="589" height="193" />\r\n\r\nLots of people do this last one. You’ll rarely get a follow from a group recommendation. There are way too many choices, and Twitter is too fast for making choices.\r\n\r\nThe only decision to make is whether to click on ‘that’ message or ‘this’ one, and if you’ve suggested 5 #FFs in one message you’ll be ignored or worse, labelled a spammer. Whereas, by giving a legitimate reason to follow someone people are more likely to listen.\r\n\r\nLooking at both of the cases above, which one are you most likely to act on?\r\n\r\nThere is a nice cartoon about the #FollowFriday theme made by <a href="https://twitter.com/oatmeal">The Oatmeal</a> (<a href="http://theoatmeal.com/comics/follow_friday">link to website</a>) that I copy here below:\r\n\r\n<!-- ADDING INSERT FROM OATMEAL ----->\r\n<div class="panel first floor3"><a href="http://twitter.com/oatmeal"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/theoatmeal-img/comics/follow_friday/header.png" alt="Minor Differences" /></a></div>\r\n<div class="panel floor3"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/theoatmeal-img/comics/follow_friday/1.png" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div class="panel floor3"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/theoatmeal-img/comics/follow_friday/2.png" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div class="panel floor3"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/theoatmeal-img/comics/follow_friday/3.png" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div class="panel floor3"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/theoatmeal-img/comics/follow_friday/4.png" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div class="panel floor3"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/theoatmeal-img/comics/follow_friday/5.png" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div class="panel floor3"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/theoatmeal-img/comics/follow_friday/6.png" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div class="panel floor3"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/theoatmeal-img/comics/follow_friday/7.png" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div class="panel floor3"><a href="http://twitter.com/oatmeal"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/theoatmeal-img/comics/follow_friday/8.png" alt="" /></a></div>\r\n<!-- END OF INSERT FROM OATMEAL -->\r\n\r\nSending a mutual #FF simply because someone has #FF’d you is not an authentic reason to send them one too. Don’t make this your reason for doing so – others will see through it and won’t appreciate a suggestion to follow someone who tweets nonsense all day. Please, be considered and genuine in your recommendations.\r\n\r\nLastly, If you’re lucky enough to receive an #FF, thank the person in a reply tweet.  It is also a nice thing to do.\r\n\r\nNow you know all about #FollowFriday, who will you be showing your appreciation for next time?\r\n\r\nNot only is #FF useful for personal use, but it’s an excellent practice in your business.\r\n\r\nBy implementing it, you can receive a tons of new quality followers over time, use it as a great way to recommend a fellow business that you feel strongly about, gives you a chance to thank others for retweeting your content and at the end of the day, someone might #FF you back if you give them a shout out!', 'Twitter #FollowFriday (#FF)', 'Okay, Many of you have seen the #FF on the bird''s social network, but you never quite understand what it is and how it''s used for.  I''ll try to describe to you what it should be and also what it is.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'twitter-followfriday-ff', '', '', '2016-11-08 14:45:29', '2016-11-08 14:45:29', '', 0, 'https://ivanjr.website/?p=121', 0, 'post', '', 0),
