(147, 1, '2016-11-10 21:31:16', '2016-11-10 21:31:16', 'With the awkward - to say the least - result in the American Election 2016 a new trending topic in Twitter has appeared.  It''s the <a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=%23OrangePresident&amp;src=ivanjr.website">#OrangePresident</a>.  It came to be due to now President-Elect Trump''s cutis.  It seems his artificial tan preference is more a carrot-like tint.\r\n\r\nA parallel to Netflix''s series is inevitable in this case and the picture that is on top of the post is also a new <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meme">meme</a> that is very popular on the major Social Networks.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-149" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Oitnb-netflix.jpeg" alt="Orange is the New Black" width="400" height="419" />\r\n\r\nOne thing though that was unexpected was that this would bring a side-effect popularity for a three piece Japanese band called <a href="http://orange-president.com/">The Orange President</a>. They are "Osaka three-piece band" (大阪発スリーピースバンド) as they refer to themselves in their website. They have been active since 1999 and in their site you get in touch with them and see the schedule of upcoming shows. The use of an online translator like Google Translate will help if you don''t read Japanese. ;)\r\n\r\nIf you got curious of how they sound like listen to this 30 second Youtube video.\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/XZU7nb94GDw\r\n\r\nIt''s nice these side-effects that the internet provides us with.  We discover new things and new people that otherwise we would not have had the change to.\r\n\r\nWell, good luck to the new president-elect #OrangePresident and also to the Osaka band The Orange President. Let both be successful in the years ahead.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'About the #OrangePresident tag', 'In this post I bring a curiosity about the #OrangePresident hashtag.  It has given extra boost to a Japanese 3-piece band called OrangePresident.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about-the-orangepresident-tag', '', '', '2016-11-11 15:38:11', '2016-11-11 15:38:11', '', 0, 'https://ivanjr.website/?p=147', 0, 'post', '', 0),
