(156, 1, '2017-01-27 17:18:33', '2017-01-27 17:18:33', 'First of all what is DigitalOcean (<em>yes, it''s spelled as one word, with letters "D" and "O" capitalized as they refer to in their own website</em>) and why bother?  Well, if you are a content reader only and you do not develop sites nor want to know about it you may stop the reading right here.  This post is more directed to the developer community or even to the ones who have their own website or wish to have one.  Also the ones who play around with <a href="https://www.raspberrypi.org/">RaspberryPi</a> just to try out Linux you can also benefit from this.\r\n\r\nDigitalOcean is "<a href="https://www.digitalocean.com/company/press/">a simple and robust cloud computing platform, designed for developers.</a>"  This is how they refer to themselves.  By this statement they are trying to differentiate themselves from other services like Amazon''s AWS.  In this matter, I really do agree.  It''s different even though some use cases are coincidental between both.  Still from their site I''d like to show what they claim is their key differentiators.\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>Key Differentiatiors:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Simple Control Panel</strong> – DigitalOcean''s command center makes configuring cloud servers and development frameworks simple and intuitive.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Active Developer Community</strong> – DigitalOcean''s <a href="https://www.digitalocean.com/community/">community pages</a> are continually updated and moderated. Developers will find numerous tutorials, a robust Q &amp; A section, and myriad community projects.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Professional hosting starting at $5 per month</strong> – DigitalOcean''s transparent and simple pricing model starts at $5 per month and offers hourly billing.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>SSD-only cloud</strong> – DigitalOcean''s servers use only high-performance Solid State Disks. Their speed directly benefits the performance of hosted web sites and applications. All DigitalOcean cloud servers are live and configurable in less than one minute.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Linux distributions/one-click installations</strong> – DigitalOcean offers six popular Linux distributions that can be automatically pre-installed upon deployment of a server: Ubuntu, CentOS, Debian, Fedora, CoreOS and FreeBSD. A multitude of application packages can be installed with just one click, including LAMP, LEMP, and MEAN; also development frameworks Ruby on Rails, Django and Docker; as well as popular applications like eCommerce software Magento, CMS solutions Wordpress and Ghost, and MediaWiki.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\nNow, after reading the above points and being a customer for around 6 months now I can acknowledge the claims. What''s interesting is the idea of a "Droplet".  A droplet can be seen as a computer that you''ll own and pay per use that it''s active.  I''ll share below some images:\r\n<h4>Droplets</h4>\r\nWhen creating your Droplet you can choose which OS you want.  It''s like choosing to format your computer to a specified operating system.  For each of the options you can also choose the version of the OS.  And remember: All options are using SSD (Solid State Device) so it''s super fast.  I''m more of a Debian type of guy, so I chose Debian Jessie for me.  But Ubuntu is really popular.\r\n\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-158" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Droplets.png" alt="droplets" width="990" height="346" />\r\n\r\nAfter that you get the straight forward option of choosing the size of the droplet.  Prices are right there so you know ahead of time what you''re paying for.  I''m using the $5/month and I''m really happy with it.  I have 2 different websites running in this version and the 20GB is more than enough for my needs.\r\n\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-159" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/chooseAsize.png" alt="droplet-choosing a size" width="989" height="465" />\r\n\r\nFrom there you have your machine (I should say Droplet) almost ready.  You can add more block storage if needed and choose some additional options like enabling Private Networking, Backups, IPv6 and some other cool stuff.  All adds up to the final price, but you know ahead of time.  What''s missing is to choose where in the world you want this machine (droplet) to be.  As of the time of writing this post the options are:\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-160" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/chooseAplace.png" alt="droplets-choose a location" width="992" height="345" />\r\n\r\nWhat''s cool is that if you need to create more than 1 machine (droplet) you can do that and literally it''s takes less than 10 seconds.  The GIF below is not in high speed.  Take a look!\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-161" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/create-5fe2f870.gif" alt="creating a droplet gif" width="700" height="550" />\r\n<h4>Outside review and opinion from Social Media</h4>\r\nThe site <a href="http://hostingreviews.io">HostingReviews.io</a> is an interesting place to go to see what people are saying about the service on Social Media. DigitalOcean has been doing really good among other competitors as you may see from the below graph extracted from their <a href="http://hostingreviews.io/web-hosting/digitalocean">site.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://hostingreviews.io/web-hosting/digitalocean"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-164" src="https://ivanjr.website/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/hostingreviews.png" alt="hostingreviews.io" width="1181" height="264" /></a>\r\n\r\nSo, I guess if you have reached this far you noticed that I became a fan of DigitalOcean, right?  It''s true.  And I can tell you that I haven''t spent a dime in the first 2 months because I was someone else''s referral.\r\n<h4>Coupon time - Get $10 to test DigitalOcean</h4>\r\nDo you want $10 credit to test DigitalOcean?  Simply use my <a href="https://m.do.co/c/d3d42a44f7a8">referral code</a> and you''ll get the $10 credit and you can monitor the spending of this credit going in the billing details.  That gives you 2 months of the $5/month plan for you to test the system.  If you decide to stay and end up paying  the sum of $25 I''ll get that in credit also.  So it''s a win-win for us!  Don''t forget to use the referral link if you''ll be trying out the system, ok?\r\n\r\n<a href="https://m.do.co/c/d3d42a44f7a8">https://m.do.co/c/d3d42a44f7a8 </a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'DigitalOcean Review', 'In this post you''ll be able to see my experience with DigitalOcean and what I think about its service.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'digitalocean-review', '', '', '2017-02-06 16:44:44', '2017-02-06 16:44:44', '', 0, 'https://ivanjr.website/?p=156', 0, 'post', '', 0),
